1
00:00:00,542 --> 00:00:03,584
As for the names, like I told you, they’re all fake names

2
00:00:04,751 --> 00:00:05,959
Abu Talha

3
00:00:06,667 --> 00:00:07,876
Abu Aisha

4
00:00:08,292 --> 00:00:11,083
Any of these names, they never call each other by real names

5
00:00:11,417 --> 00:00:12,792
So you don’t know what his name is

6
00:00:14,125 --> 00:00:16,167
And when you leave, you can’t see who is torturing you

7
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:17,834
Because your eyes are blindfolded

8
00:00:18,500 --> 00:00:19,751
And you don’t know who he actually is

9
00:00:31,042 --> 00:00:34,626
Interviewer: What were the nationalities
of those who were flogging or torturing?

10
00:00:35,459 --> 00:00:39,876
I don’t know exactly what their nationalities were

11
00:00:41,959 --> 00:00:44,125
Like I told you, some of them spoke Arabic

12
00:00:44,167 --> 00:00:47,459
And some of them spoke Russian, I think

13
00:00:48,083 --> 00:00:51,292
And some of them spoke Chinese or Japanese

14
00:00:51,334 --> 00:00:53,584
Or something similar, I don’t know

15
00:00:54,417 --> 00:01:00,292
And some of them spoke a language that sounded Indian or Pakistani

16
00:01:00,918 --> 00:01:02,250
Some of them spoke like that

17
00:01:02,334 --> 00:01:06,626
Because their Arabic was really bad

18
00:01:07,542 --> 00:01:09,500
They only knew a few Arabic words

19
00:01:10,626 --> 00:01:13,500
Those were the same ones who weren’t Iraqis

20
00:01:14,125 --> 00:01:17,083
They spoke a few Arabic words very badly

21
00:01:17,459 --> 00:01:19,584
So it was obvious they weren’t Iraqis
